value.name: Veeru Devgan - Wikipedia
value.snippet: Veeru Devgan (25 June 1934 — 27 May 2019) was an Indian action choreographer, actor and film director who worked in Bollywood films. He worked on more than 200 Indian films including Roti Kapada Aur Makaan, Kranti, Mr. Natwarlal, Prem Rog, Phool Aur Kaante, Jigar and Ram Teri Ganga Maili. He is the father of actor Ajay Devgn.

value.snippet: Veeru Devgan was born in a Saraswat Brahmin family in 1934 (Age: 85 years, at the time of death) in Amritsar, British India. To become an actor, he left home with his three friends in 1957 and he along with friends were sent to jail as they were travelling by train without ticket.

value.name: Veeru Devgan Age, Wife, Death, Children, Family, Biography & More
value.snippet: He was born in Amritsar, Punjab, India. In 1957, at the age of 14, he left Amritsar and moved to Bombay (now, Mumbai) along with his friends with a dream of becoming successful and famous. They took a train to Mumbai but didn’t buy tickets. Consequently, the whole squad was caught by the police at Virar Station.

value.name: Veeru Devgan - Bio, Age, Net Worth, Height, Nationality, Facts
value.snippet: Veeru Devgan was born on 25 June 1934 and he was 84 years old at the time of his demise on 27 May 2019. Veeru’s birthplace is Amritsar, Punjab, India, and at the time of his demise, he resided in Mumbai, Maharashtra, India. He is the patriarch of the infamous Devgan family, one of the most well-known Hindi film families in India.
